mcmFrConnectTable.name: mcmFrConnectTable

mcmFrConnectIfIndexLocal.name: mcmFrConnectIfIndexLocal
mcmFrConnectIfIndexLocal.description: NAME = ; DESC = When switch type is FRDCE, the \ ifIndex of the local DCE interface. \ (Analogous to the ifIndex pointer in \ MIB II Interfaces Group, but specific \ to the FR End-to-End Connections \ table.) When switch type is HTDS, the \ ifIndex of the local WAN interface. \ (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmFrConnectDLCILocal.name: mcmFrConnectDLCILocal
mcmFrConnectDLCILocal.description: NAME = ; DESC = The DLCI value on the local DCE \ interface. Always 16 if HTDS. \ (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmFrConnectConnectId.name: mcmFrConnectConnectId
mcmFrConnectConnectId.description: NAME = ; DESC = The Connect ID of this SPVC mapping. \ Used to associate SVCs and Connect \ mappings. (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmFrConnectIfIndexRemote.name: mcmFrConnectIfIndexRemote
mcmFrConnectIfIndexRemote.description: NAME = ; DESC = *******NOTE: THIS OBJECT IS OBSOLETE******* This information is no longer useful since \ the remote ifindex is configured in with the \ ConncectDNA when required.\ The ifIndex of the remote DCE interface. \ (To be carried in the user-to-user signaling \ of the SVC call setup to the remote access device.) \ (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmFrConnectDLCIRemote.name: mcmFrConnectDLCIRemote
mcmFrConnectDLCIRemote.description: NAME = ; DESC = The DLCI value on the remote DCE \ interface. (To be carried in the user-to-user \ signaling of the SVC call setup to the remote \ access device.) (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmFrConnectIfIndexSVC.name: mcmFrConnectIfIndexSVC
mcmFrConnectIfIndexSVC.description: NAME = ; DESC = Beginning with release 3.0, the value of this \ object indicates the ifIndex value corresponding \ to the tunneling PVC in which the SVC is established. \ Prior to release 3.0, this object indicates the \ ifIndex of the local DTE interface on \ which this SVC is to be established with the \ remote access device. (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmFrConnectDNARemote.name: mcmFrConnectDNARemote
mcmFrConnectDNARemote.description: NAME = ; DESC = The DNA of the remote node with which the \ the SVC will be established. (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmFrConnectSVCDLCI.name: mcmFrConnectSVCDLCI
mcmFrConnectSVCDLCI.description: NAME = ; DESC = The DLCI value of the SVC once the SVC \ has been established. (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmFrConnectDCEPVCLMIState.name: mcmFrConnectDCEPVCLMIState
mcmFrConnectDCEPVCLMIState.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates \ whether the local DCE considers the local \ PVC associated with this mapping active (1) \ or inactive (2). (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmFrConnectSVCState.name: mcmFrConnectSVCState
mcmFrConnectSVCState.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates \ whether the local DCE considers the \ SVC associated with this mapping active (1) \ or inactive (2). (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmFrConnectConnType.name: mcmFrConnectConnType
mcmFrConnectConnType.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of this object indicates \ whether this end of the SPVC segment \ initiated the SVC call, master (1); \ or not, slave (1). (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmFrConnectLastChange.name: mcmFrConnectLastChange
mcmFrConnectLastChange.description: NAME = ; DESC = The value of MIB II's sysUpTime at \ the time this PVC mapping entered its \ current operations state in the high to \ low direction. (Operational); HELP = ; CAPABILITIES = ;

mcmFrConnectDisconnectReason.name: mcmFrConnectDisconnectReason

mcmFrConnectSwitchType.name: mcmFrConnectSwitchType

mcmMPANLConnSVCSetupPriority.name: mcmMPANLConnSVCSetupPriority
